name: Jordan Chiles
summary: Romanian gymnast could replace Jordan Chiles as bronze medalist in floor exercise after a court ruling. Chiles, who initially won bronze, has filed an appeal to the judges and may have to return it. The gymnastics federation has reinstated the initial score, potentially leading to Chiles losing her medal. Despite the controversy, Chiles has remained positive, meeting celebrities and expressing excitement for her future. She will return to competition at the Olympics on Monday and will also return to UCLA for the 2025 season.

name: NASCAR
summary: The NASCAR Cup Series is currently on hold, with the next race scheduled for Sunday, August 11th at Richmond Raceway. The series will then break again for the Olympics before resuming on August 21st with the Cup Series race at the Daytona International Speedway. The 2025 NASCAR lineup is expected to include Daniel Suarez remaining at Trackhouse Racing Team. The starting lineup for the Cook Out 400 race at Richmond Raceway is now available. The NASCAR Cup Series schedule for 2024 has been released, including start times and TV networks. NASCAR is facing financial challenges due to a decline in sponsor revenues, leading to talks with teams. Legacy Motor Club NASCAR team has undergone an organizational shakeup, and the 2025 NASCAR playoff schedule is likely to include Talladega Superspeedway in the semifinals.

name: Shelby McEwen
summary: American high jumper Shelby McEwen secured a silver medal in the men's high jump at the 2024 Olympics in Paris. McEwen advanced to the final after a successful preliminary round, making him one of the contenders for the gold medal. In a dramatic turn of events, McEwen tied with Australian Hamish Kerr for first place, but declined an offer to share the gold medal in a jump-off. Kerr ultimately won the gold, while McEwen settled for silver. McEwen's performance marked a significant achievement for the Mississippi native, who received widespread praise and recognition for his determination and skill.

name: Lilo and Stitch live-action
summary: Disney's beloved animated classic "Lilo & Stitch" is getting a live-action remake, and fans are eagerly anticipating its release in the summer of 2025. The first glimpse of the CGI Stitch has been revealed, showcasing the iconic extraterrestrial's familiar mischievous nature. The live-action adaptation will encompass the heartwarming themes of the original, with Lilo and her alien companion embarking on a journey of friendship, acceptance, and the importance of family. The remake promises to bring a fresh perspective while retaining the essence of the original, offering a nostalgic and immersive experience for both seasoned fans and new audiences alike.

name: Justin Fields
summary: Justin Fields, the starting quarterback for the Pittsburgh Steelers, made his preseason debut against the Houston Texans. While he showed flashes of potential, his performance was marred by multiple fumbles. Head coach Mike Tomlin acknowledged that the fumbles overshadowed Fields' positive plays and described them as "undone." Despite the miscues, several reports suggest that Fields is still the main focus of the Steelers' training camp and could potentially challenge for the starting quarterback role. Despite Russell Wilson's absence due to a calf injury, Fields is expected to receive playing time in the upcoming preseason games to improve his performance and address his fumble issue.

name: Olympic marathon
summary: The 2024 Paris Olympics marathon course is renowned for its historic landmarks and challenging hills, as highlighted in "The view from Paris" article. Despite its reputation as "the most hellish marathon in Olympic history," as described in "It’s the Most Hellish Marathon in Olympic History. So I Had to Run It.", two friends embark on a journey to conquer the marathon in "Spurred by faith and friendship." Ethiopian runner Tamirat Tola's historic victory over Kenya's dominance in the men's marathon is captured in "Ethiopian runner Tamirat Tola wins men's marathon at Paris Olympics to end Kenya dominance." However, Olympic legend Eliud Kipchoge ends his Olympic career on a somber note after a disappointing performance in "Eliud Kipchoge announces the end of his Olympic career after 'worst marathon'." Advanced running shoes are revolutionizing the Olympic marathon, as explored in "How supershoes are redefining the Olympic marathon." "The Olympic Marathon Course Is a Torture Test. That’s by Design." emphasizes the course's intentional difficulty, while "‘There Are going to Be People Walking:’ A Look at the Grueling Olympic Marathon Course" provides a detailed analysis of its challenges. Ethiopia's Tola's triumph and Kipchoge's departure from Olympic competition are further highlighted in "Ethiopia's Tola storms to men's marathon gold as Kipchoge drops out." Finally, "When Are The Marathons At The 2024 Paris Olympic Games: What To Know" provides information on the upcoming marathon events at the 2024 Paris Olympics.
